1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2641, Page 15, Section 195.900, Lines
2 135-139, by deleting said lines and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
3
4 "11. (1) The provisions of this section shall become effective November 12, 2026, for:
5 (a) Hemp-derived cannabinoid products that:
6 a. Contain cannabinoids that are not capable of being naturally produced by a Cannabis
7 sativa L. plant;
8 b. Contain cannabinoids that are capable of being naturally produced by a Cannabis
9 sativa L. plant but that were synthesized or manufactured outside the plant;
10 c. Are sold, distributed, or marketed to a consumer as a product that can be smokable or
11 vapeable in the form of raw plant material, flower, or bud material and that contain any amount
12 of tetrahydrocannabinolic acid; or
13 d. Are sold, distributed, or marketed to a consumer in the form of any solid candy,
14 gummy, chewable product, tablet, capsule, oil, baked good, or other solid edible product and that
15 contain delta-9 tetrahydrocannabinol derived from hemp in any amount that exceeds naturally
16 occurring concentrations in the source hemp plant material; and
17 (b) Except as provided in subdivision (2) of this subsection, all other hemp-derived
18 cannabinoid products not described in paragraph (a) of this subdivision.
19 (2) For all other hemp-derived cannabinoid products not described in paragraph (a) of
20 subdivision (1) of this subsection, the provisions of this section shall become effective
21 November 12, 2026, except that if Congress delays the effective date of federal hemp restrictions
22 under 7 U.S.C. Section 1639o on or before November 12, 2026, this section shall apply to such
23 products only during any period in which such federal restrictions prohibiting such products.";
24 and
25
26 Further amend said bill and page, Section B, Lines 1-4, by deleting said section and lines; and
27
28 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
29 accordingly.
